    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "oh okay, that makes sense. a bit nerve wracking though lol. so what happens if the inspection comes back and it's like, a total mess? if i find structural damage, can i just get my money back from the escrow account or is it a whole legal battle to get it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the inspection reveals major issues, you usually have options before resorting to a legal fight. First, you can negotiate with the seller to have them fix the problems, or they might offer you a price reduction to cover the repairs. If negotiations fail, you can typically back out of the contract entirely, and because your contract likely has inspection contingencies, you would be entitled to have your earnest money returned from escrow. It's best to follow the exact terms laid out in your purchase agreement to ensure a smooth process.",
      "source": "target",
