      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow company, often a title or real estate firm, is the official custodian of those funds. They are legally bound by the contract to hold the money securely until all conditions are met. Their job is to act as a neutral referee, ensuring neither party can prematurely claim the money without following the agreed-upon steps. They are responsible for following the established legal procedures for releasing or returning the funds.",
